<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="particular-adj">particular <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /pə'tɪkjələ(r)/    美 /pər'tɪkjələr/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>[只用于名词前] 特定的</strong></h4>
<p>used to emphasize that you are talking about one person, thing, time, etc. and not about others (specific)：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He did not show up on that particular day. 
他并没有在那一天露面。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The giant panda eats only one particular type of bamboo.
大熊猫只吃某一种竹子。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>特别的；格外的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I have <strong>nothing particular</strong> to do this evening. 
今晚我没有什么特别的事要做。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We must pay particular attention to this point. 
我们必须要特别注意这一点。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.<strong>讲究的；挑剔的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a particular customer 
挑剔的顾客</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She is very <strong>particular about / over</strong> her appearance.
她很在意自己的外表。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="in-particular">in particular</h3>
<p>1.<strong>尤其；特别：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Parents and coaches in particular should act as better examples for children. 
父母和教练尤其要给孩子们树立更好的榜样。</p><footer>2008 上海</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Are you doing anything in particular this weekend?
这个周末你有什么特别的安排吗？</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>She has already tried her best. Please don’t be too particular <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ her job.   （2011 江西改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. about / over  </p></div>